The Northern Governors Forum has described former President of Nigeria, Olusegun Obasanjo, as a leader who gave his best to Nigeria and humanity. The Chairman of the forum and Governor of Plateau, Simon Lalong, in a congratulatory message issued on Wednesday in Jos by his Director of Press and Public Affairs, Dr Makut Macham, on his 83rd birthday, praised Chief Obasanjo for his visionary and patriotic service to Nigeria, the African Continent and the world. Lalong lauded Obasanjo’s commitment to the growth of democracy, good governance and human rights, which he had pursued in and out of office and under different platforms across the globe. The chairman urged the former President not to relent in offering his wealth of wisdom and experience to the present leaderships at all levels, especially in the fight against corruption and insecurity in Nigeria He wished him more years of good health, God’s wisdom and protection as he continued serving Nigeria, Africa and the world. Obasanjo born on March 5, 1937 served as a military head of state from 1976 to 1979 then president of Nigeria from 1999 to 2007.